 for quick, healthy meals, and pasta fits this description.</span></li></ul><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" id="answer3_unbox_6" unbox="extra_examples"><span class="box_title">Extra Examples</span><ul class="examples" htag="ul" hclass="examples"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">A man fitting your description was seen entering the building.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">I realized to my horror that the description of the killer could fit me.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">Police have arrested two men matching the descriptions of the robbers.</span></li></ul></span></div>      </li></ol></span> <span class="idm-g" sk="answertonameof" bord="y" id="answer_idmg_2"><div class="top-container"><div class="top-g" id="answer_topg_5"><div class="webtop"><span class="idm" id="answer_idm_2">answer to the name of something</span> </div></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="answer_sng_8" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="dis-g"><span class="wrap">(</span><span class="dtxt">especially of a pet animal</span><span class="wrap">)</span></span></span> <span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">to be called something</span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">The dog was an ugly brute, answering to the name of Spike.</span></li></ul>      </li></ol></span></div><aside class="phrasal_verb_links" id="answer_pvgs_1" hclass="phrasal_verb_links" xt="pvlist" htag="aside"><span class="unbox">Phrasal Verbs</span><ul class="pvrefs"><li class="li"><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/answer-back#answerback2_e" title="answer back definition"><span class="xr-g" href="answerback2_e" id="answer_xrg_14" dict="all" bord="n"><span class="xh">answer back</span></span></a></li><li class="li"><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/answer-for#answerfor2_e" title="answer for definition"><span class="xr-g" bord="n" dict="all" id="answer_xrg_15" href="answerfor2_e"><span class="xh">answer for</span></span></a></li><li class="li"><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/answer-to#answerto2_e" title="answer to definition"><span class="xr-g" href="answerto2_e" id="answer_xrg_16" bord="n" dict="all"><span class="xh">answer to</span></span></a></li></ul></aside><span class="dictlink-g"><span class="dictlink">See <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/answer_2" title=" definition in American English
